# Cloudflare Pages rewrite rules (backward compatibility).
#
# The repo was restructured: loader.js and upsell.css moved up out of
# /upsells/{js,css}/ into /js/ and /css/ at the repo root. Live Kajabi
# upsell pages still embed the OLD script URL (/upsells/js/loader.js),
# and browsers that cached the OLD loader.js will try to fetch the OLD
# CSS URL (/upsells/css/upsell.css). These 200 rewrites keep both
# paths resolving to the new files without a client redirect, so the
# old Kajabi embeds continue working indefinitely — no Kajabi-side
# change is required to deploy this refactor safely.
#
# Format: <source>  <destination>  <status>
# status 200 = rewrite (serve target content under source URL)
# status 301 = permanent redirect (not used here — would force URL change)
#
# Remove these lines only after every Kajabi upsell embed has been
# migrated to the new /js/loader.js URL AND enough time has passed
# for browser caches to expire the old loader.js (days, realistically).

/upsells/js/loader.js     /js/loader.js     200
/upsells/css/upsell.css   /css/upsell.css   200
